Reasoning: The paper focuses on the use of tactile sensors for autonomous learning of manipulation tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The learning algorithm used is Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO), which is a popular reinforcement learning algorithm in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the role of sensory information on learning rates and performance, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses a simulated hand and ball, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or systems and control (cs.SY).
